Broma

Una broma es una maniobra, trampa o truco que se le hace a alguien a propósito para que se sienta ridiculizado, engañado o victimizado, normalmente por humor. En muchas bromas existe una crueldad inherente que las hace difíciles de diferenciar del acoso, el sadismo, el vandalismo o el hooliganismo.

En la cultura occidental suele dedicarse un día al año para llevar a cabo bromas, como el día de los Santos Inocentes en la mayoría de los países de habla hispana, o el día de las bromas de abril en otros países. Otro día común para bromas es el día de Halloween, bajo la forma del «truco o trato». También se hacen bromas en las fiestas de cumpleaños de adolescentes y adultos (principalmente en Latinoamérica), así como en carnaval. Las bromas en las que se utiliza el teléfono como medio se denominan bromas telefónicas.

La masificación de las Web 2.0 ha revitalizado la producción de bromas, como consecuencia de la facilidad que entregan estos sitios para compartir la información, el nuevo impulso que han tenido las bromas, ha convertido a la época actual, en una edad de oro, por la proliferación de bromas caseras amateur y profesionales. Youtube realizó una gráfica en la cual muestra el explosivo crecimiento que han tenido las visualizaciones de vídeos y canales dedicados a las bromas.




Streich

Der Streich (auch Schabernack, Jokus und Ulk) ist eine mutwillige, listige oder hinterlistige Handlung gegen andere, die keine schwerwiegenden rechtlichen Folgen hat.

Etymologie

Das Substantiv Streich bedeutete zunächst – und bis heute – auch „Schlag, Hieb“ (vgl. engl. to strike) und fand seit dem 15. Jahrhundert häufige Verwendung in der Zusammensetzung Backenstreich. Im 17. Jahrhundert gewann es als unerwarteter Schlag oder überraschende Unternehmung an Bedeutung, beispielsweise beim militärischen Handstreich. Die Redewendung „jemandem einen Streich spielen“ stammt aus dem 18. Jahrhundert. (Jokus leitet sich aus dem Lateinischen iocus ab. Die Herkunft der Wortes Schabernack ist ungeklärt. Ulk kommt ursprünglich durch die Studentensprache aus dem Niederdeutschen und bedeutete „Lärm, Unruhe, Händel“.)




Practical joke

A practical joke (also known as a prank, gag, jape or shenanigan) is a mischievous trick or joke played on someone, generally causing the victim to experience embarrassment, perplexity, confusion, or discomfort. Practical jokes range from confidence tricks or hoaxes in that the victim finds out, or is let in on the joke, rather than being talked into handing over money or other valuables. Practical jokes or pranks are generally lighthearted, reversible and non-permanent, and aim to make the victim feel foolish or victimised to a degree, but may also involve cruelty verging on bullying if performed without appropriate finesse.




Humour potache

L'humour potache est un humour moqueur portant peu à conséquence, qui n'offense pas autrui, et qui n'est pas basé sur un mensonge. Le mot potache fait partie du jargon scolaire et fait référence au collégien ou au lycéen.




Câmera escondida

Uma câmera escondida, também chamada de pegadinha, câmera oculta ou apanhados é uma situação forjada ou verdadeira (que pode ser chamada de brincadeira) pela produção de algum programa onde se cria um constrangimento, uma situação absurda e inesperada com alguém que supostamente ignora a armação da qual será vítima.

Hoje em dia, vários programas de TV se utilizam ou se utilizaram de pegadinhas, dentre eles os de João Kléber, Sérgio Mallandro, Silvio Santos, Gugu Liberato, Fausto Silva , Luciana Gimenez, etc. Nos Estados Unidos, o programa precursor dessa modalidade na televisão é o Candid Camera, que faz sucesso desde a década de 1950 até os dias de hoje.

Muitos telespectadores duvidam da veracidade dessas brincadeiras, que de fato, muitas vezes são forjadas a suposta vítima mas na maioria das vezes as vitimas são atraidas por ofertas tentadoras e pela oportunidade de levar uma grande vantagem, seja ao se aproximar de uma mulher jovem e bonita, ou adquirir algo por um preço irrisório .




ドッキリ

ドッキリとはバラエティ番組の表現手法のひとつ。番組進行を知らない、または虚偽の進行だけ知らされている出演者をだましたりイタズラを仕掛けたりして、出演者の反応を楽しむという手法。

description: Decomposition is one of the most important biological processes there is, and is a critical part of the carbon cycle. Everything that lives eventually dies and decomposes. Most plants are not eaten by herbivores. Instead, they eventually die, fall to the ground and decompose. How does this process work? This professionally produced and narrated video describes how decomposition happens, and the role of microorganisms in this process. It was produced for the Interactive Model of Leaf Decomposition (IMOLD) by the University of Toledo's Center for Creative Instruction in collaboration with Dr. Michael N. Weintraub and Dr. Daryl L. Moorhead.
title: How Decomposition Works

description:
Instructional video on how to operate and refill your EGO-CE6 E-cigarette from Infinite Vapour.

Extra Tips:
A new battery MUST be charged for a minimum of 6 hours, ignoring and indicator lights (first time charge only) 2--3 hours will fully charge your battery after 1st optimum charge.
Always fill the cartomiser slightly tilted and place bottle tip side to ensure no liquid goes down the centre hole (air intake) if liquid gets into the air intake, a quick sharp strong draw usually resolves it.
For optimum vapour and flavour replace the CE6 wick regularly, a 20 per day smoker should change approx every 1-2 months.
If you experience a slight burning taste as the cartomiser empties of liquid, roll the E-liquid around to ensure the wicks are soaked in e liquid. this usually does the trick.
If after 30+ days your device doesn't vape, its usually time to replace your wicks.
Always keep spare wicks, Try to keep a spare battery if you only have a single unit.  
Do not hold cartomiser upside down longer than a second.
Always tilt e cigarette at a downward angle when vaping.
Take extra care of your e cigarette, do not drop or damage as your unit will stop working.

More info available at https://www.infinitevapour.com
title: EGO-CE6 Starter Video by Infinite Vapour

description:
Every orphan dreams of their own family and home. However, many Russians who grew up in orphanages have their dreams shattered when they see the housing which they are entitled to from the state. Dank, dark and dilapidated: a flat which orphan graduate Elena Zatelepina received from the government when she turned 18 looks more like a prime candidate for demolition than a family home. Still, the 22-year-old mother of the two has been told by social services that she is stuck here. "Perhaps they have not seen this place inside," she said. "They keep telling us to repair it somehow and live here." "They showed me a paper on 'how to build a house'. I told them that I had no funds," Elena added. "I have no job, I have to take care of kids and I ended up renting a place. They said 'It is not our problem'." Elena grew up in an orphanage in the city of Tver. Under Russian law she was to receive state housing once she left the institution. The flat proposed to Elena used to belong to her mother, and despite having no money, she has been told to fix it up. The situation is absolutely desperate," Elena said. "They do not give me work because I do not have a profession. For them I do not exist. Perhaps hanging myself would be the best thing to do." Elena's case is not unusual. Those who work with orphanages in Russia say that it is when they leave the care homes that they need most help.
RT on Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/RTnews
RT on Twitter: http://twitter.com/RT_com
title: Homeless Alone: 'Cute orphans' grow into desperate adults

description:
My son and I took our new DPMS Panther Arms .308 Oracle LR-308 out today for the first time. We have a DPMS quad rail handguard (with micro gas block) installed and a Nikon ProStaff 3-9x40mm scope (w/ BDC Reticle).

We were at the range for three hours and only shot maybe 60 rounds. The reason is due to the manufacturer-expected break-in procedure (clean bore/chamber after each round, etc.....). 

By the time we made this video, we were finally up to shooting five shots at a time. Being the novice "snipers" that we are, we managed to get 1-1/2 inch groups at 100 yards using a variety of 7.62 and .308 ammo. The 7.62 Federal Lake City ammo was much more accurate than our more expensive .308 rounds (a mix of Winchester and Federal and grains). I'm sure we'll get tighter groups in time.

This rifle is sweet. Not a single failure/jam. Had a couple of issues getting the pmag locked in place (thought it was all the way in when it wasn't). No big deal. Just gotta push a little harder.

I definitely recommend this rifle. I enjoyed shooting it much more than our previous AR15 that we sold to get this one. A .308 just makes a much more impressive BOOM!

By the way, sorry for the wind noise in the audio. A cell phone can only do so much!
title: DPMS Panther Arms .308 Oracle LR-308 - First time out.

description:
Victor Wanyama came off the bench to score his first Southampton goal and continue their impressive start to the season with a win over 10-man Swansea.

The midfielder produced the game's one real moment of class with a neat 12-yard finish with 10 minutes remaining.

The Saints had dominated the second half thanks largely to the sending off of Swansea's Wilfried Bony for two clumsy fouls just before the break.

Swansea had started stronger but were unable to hold out with 10 men.  The win moves Southampton up to second in the table and continues what is a remarkable start to the campaign following a summer in which Ronald Koeman's predecessor as manager, Mauricio Pochettino, and five key players left St Mary's.

It represents only the third time that Saints have won three games in a row since returning to the Premier League in August 2012.

It's our BIG Celebrational 25th Anniversary COUNTRY FOLK ART CRAFT SHOW! . . .  the weekend of October 24-25-26 in Edison, NJ at the New Jersey Convention & Expo Center. Our fabulous Fall show features over 150 top artisan-crafters from across the nation! You'll love the huge array of unique and creative decorating accents, such as: beautiful artwork, handcrafted furniture and furnishing reproductions, and lighting, handwoven rugs, repurposed antiques and treasures, lace, wood cutlery, primitive furniture, framed art, paintings, textiles, candles, signs, floral designs, wearable art, home and garden decor, jewelry, adult/children's clothing and accessories, gourmet delights and so much more!
So mark your calendar and bring all your friends...You won't want to miss this fun and exciting shopping opportunity. Come see all your favorites and latest trends for fall, Halloween, the upcoming holidays and beyond . . . where you're sure to find something special for your home, garden, office, friends and family and most importantly, YOURSELF! Some great booth spaces still available. Very special 'original' pricing for our Oct. 24-26 Edison 25th Anniversary Show: 10'x10' booth only $250! Kailien Enterprsie, a professional & reliable plastic extrusion machine line manufacturer in Taiwan since 1963.
Machine working steps:
1. Pour PVC/CaCo3 powder into the raw material tub.
2. Powder will be sucked into Mixer.
3. Pour stabilizer into Mixer during mixing.
4. When reaching settled temperature, powder will be released into the Cooling unit.  
5. After cooling, powder will be sucked into Pellet Extruder
6. Vibration pellet cooling unit.
7.After being pelletized, powder will be sucked into Auto Counting Stainless Tank.
Machine working process:
Material Conveyor (PVC powder to Mixer)→KL300A 300L/600L High and Low Speed Mixer→5" Screw Transport System(Mixer to Extruder)→KK-130SP 130M/M PVC Pellet Single Screw Extruder

Introducing the ultimate retrofit. Now you can shift the color of your aquatic environment without shifting your body with the industry's first freshwater-optimized, full-spectrum (RGB+White), wireless remote controlled LED flexible strip light.

This ultra easy-to-install flexible strip light pairs super bright 6500K White LEDs with full-spectrum RGB LEDs to offer every color under the sun (and a few that aren't) controlled from a single, wireless 32-key customizable remote. 

Game-changing retrofit
The Satellite LED+ Flexible Strip Light features effects that you'll have to see to believe, plus each color is individually adjustable for endless custom color blends. Features include:
6, freshwater-optimized, color pre-sets
12, dynamic effects including: cloud cover, fading lunar, storm, lightning, dusk and more
4, memory buttons for saving custom color blends
Pause/play each mode on-demand

Freshwater is cool again
Drawing on our years of expertise in both fresh and marine aquarium product development we have created another industry first -- a full-spectrum, wireless remote controlled, customizable flexible strip light that was engineered from the ground up for freshwater aquarium environments. Making it the perfect choice for a beginner looking for a fast and easy way to dramatically improve their existing lighting set-up, or a seasoned veteran seeking a significant upgrade.

Excitement installed in minutes
Simply unroll the strip light and cut to the appropriate length. Then, remove the adhesive backing and stick into place. We've also included clips and hardware for more custom installations.

What's in the box
1 -- Adhesive-backed 44" Satellite LED+ flexible strip

Balam Kheera is Indian name given to Kigelia africana popularly used in African Traditional medicine system. The Indian Traditional Healers use it in form of tens of formulations. Most of these Formulations are not known even by the African Traditional Healers. During recent visit to Forest Pankaj Oudhia found it with the roadside herb seller. Pankaj Oudhia is documenting the knowledge of Indian Traditional Healers using such African Traditional Medicines in innovative ways. You can get details from pankajoudhia.com

Description: Rheumatism can affect all joints within the body, triggered by the own immune system. Inflammation is elicited above all by a messenger substance -- the so called TNF alpha. It attracts aggressive phagocytes into the joint space and activates them. The phagocytes -- which are rather meant to eliminate pathogenic germs, now attack the cartilage layer and later also the bone.
To stop this process, antibodies are injected. They bind the TNF alpha and neutralize it. Thus the messenger substance is blocked, the phagocytes are no longer activated and the inflammation within the joints can resolve.
title: B 007 TNF-alpha - SD PAL/ B 007 TNF-alpha factor  - SD PAL

description: A middle age male presented with anemia and positive FOBT. He has von Willebrand's disease (2M) and idiopathic thrombocytopenia. CT colonography was performed initially because patient was concerned of the complications of colonoscopy. This was reported as normal. Hematochezia recurred and he agreed to colonoscopy. This revealed a 10mm polyp in the sigmoid colon that was removed with snare polypectomy. One prophylactic hemostatic clip was placed. Three days later hematochezia recurred. Repeat colonoscopy revealed bleeding from post polypectomy site. The clip had fallen off. Hemostasis was achieved with one clip. An extra clip was applied as "insurance"

description:
http://www.pilatesinnerstrength.com.au

Pilates Anatomy Lesson - How To Lengthen Your Spine 

I want to teach you about a really really important muscle runds right along the entire spine.  This muscle is called the multifidus.  

What happens is that when you are engaging this muscle it actually makes your core work stronger.  So your core is going to engage much better while this muscle is activated.

It's very simple to activate and and there's a great little way that I want to show you when and how.  The muscle runs right along the entire spine, all the way through the cervical spine and up until there.   It's this long muscle which goes all the way along the spine.

To activate it , you simply want to lengthen your spine.  So if you imagine you've got a piece of string attached to the crown of the head and somebody is lifting you up by the piece of string, you're lengthening your spine. 

You're making it grow nice and long.

For the test, what I would like you to do is sit down, place your fingers on either side of your spine.  It can be anywhere along your spine.

But it would be easier to fill up three of the lumber.  So place your fingers on the spine-- either side of the spine.

Now what I want you to do is just latch.  You should feel nice and soft either side of the spine.  You shouldn't feel any muscles engaging.

Now I want you to feel like lengthening up.  Like somebody is lifting you from a piece of string attached to the crown of the head.

You should feel two muscles on either side of the spine lengthening or switching on.  Not sure if you can see it from there.  So what you want to do whenever you're exercising, running, rolling.  Whatever it is you're doing.  You want to think about lengthening your spine so that your core can engage nice and strong.

Now just doing this one, lengthen your spine and then lean forward.    You'll feel how strong these muscles engage how much they fire up.  That lengthening forward keeping your spine nice and straight when you do that, they engage again.  But, if you were to hunch over, they switch off.

If you were to lengthen and lay back you'll notice that they switch off as well.  So, that's were the correct posture becomes very very important.  You want to make sure you're not leaning back.

If you were riding a bike for instance. Obviously not a road bike.  Just a normal bike, you don't want to be leaning back, otherwise you won't have any support with the multifidus muscle or your core as well.

Make sure that when you're lengthening you're either upright or you're lengthening your spine and you're leaning forward over the bike.

So, it's a great little test for you to do if you sit down, feel either side of the spine and have a play with your posture.

If you're leaning back you'll feel it switch off, when you lean forward you feel it very very strong, and if you're lengthening that way too it will engage as well.

But, slumping forward with that poor posture you're not going to have any support and your core won't be able to engage very well.
